---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [{ params: { locale: "en" } }];
}
---

<BaseLayout
  locale="en"
  title="Privacy Policy - Utildesk"
  description="Privacy information for Utildesk, hosting, analytics and external resources."
  robots="noindex,nofollow,noarchive,nosnippet"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://tools.utildesk.de/en/privacy/" />
    <meta name="googlebot" content="noindex,nofollow,noarchive,nosnippet" />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This English version summarizes the German privacy policy for international readers. The German
      version remains the primary legal text.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Controller</h2>
    <p>The controller is the operator named in the <a href="/en/imprint/">imprint</a>.</p>

    <h2>2. Hosting and delivery</h2>
    <p>
      Utildesk is delivered through Cloudflare Pages and Cloudflare Pages Functions. Cloudflare may
      process technically necessary access data such as IP address, requested URL, user agent, HTTP
      status, timestamp and security events to provide, protect and accelerate the website.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Logs, cookies and local storage</h2>
    <p>
      The public site does not use marketing cookies. The theme preference is stored locally in your
      browser under <code>utildesk-theme</code>. The protected Ratgeber review area may set a strictly
      necessary session cookie named <code>utildesk_ratgeber_review</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      Utildesk uses privacy-friendly analytics with Umami on <code>stats.utildesk.de</code>. The
      integration is used to understand page usage and improve the site. It does not rely on advertising
      profiles across websites.
    </p>

    <h2>5. External resources and affiliate links</h2>
    <p>
      The site may load Google Fonts, favicons, logos or other technical resources from third-party
      providers. Tool entries can also contain affiliate or referral links. If you follow such a link,
      the external provider processes the request under its own privacy policy.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Machine-readable endpoints</h2>
    <p>
      Utildesk provides feeds, JSON APIs, Markdown mirrors and <code>llms.txt</code> manifests. These
      endpoints create the same technical access data as regular page views. Internal endpoints can be
      delivered with <code>X-Robots-Tag: noindex</code>.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on the applicable law, you may request access, correction, deletion, restriction of
      processing, data portability and object to processing based on legitimate interests.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Updates</h2>
    <p>This policy may be updated when the website, infrastructure or legal requirements change.</p>
  </section>
  <p>Last updated: 26 April 2026</p>
</BaseLayout>
